CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 22, 1967, pg. 13 reads: "Sitting One Out - The photographer caught two Alpha "brothers" with their dates sitting one out during the fraternity's recent summer dance. Left to right: Harry Scott, Elaine English, Charles Franklin and Lelia Evans."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Harry Scott, Elaine English, Charles Franklin, and Lelia Evans, seated at table in Pick-Roosevelt Hotel for Alpha Phi Alpha summer dance
